{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2beea1d3-f355-4d24-a737-c189250ee3ab","content":"I can help guide you through analyzing a .NET crash dump! However, the available skills here are focused on **collecting** dumps and **symbolicating** native crash logs — not post-mortem `.dmp` analysis.\n\nHere's how to analyze your dump:\n\n### Recommended Tools\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze <file.dmp>`** (cross-platform)\n   - Install: `dotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump`\n   - Key commands inside the analyzer:\n     - `clrstack` — managed call stack of the current thread\n     - `clrthreads` — list all managed threads\n     - `pe` — print the last exception\n     - `dumpheap -stat` — heap summary\n     - `setthread <id>` then `clrstack` — inspect other threads\n\n2. **WinDbg + SOS** (Windows) — richest experience for `.dmp` files\n\n3. **lldb + SOS** (Linux/macOS)\n\n### Quick Start (if you have the .NET SDK)\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-crash.dmp\n# Then inside the REPL:\n> pe           # print exception (often the root cause)\n> clrthreads   # find faulting thread\n> clrstack -a  # stack with locals\n```\n\nWould you like me to check if `dotnet-dump` is available in this environment so we can analyze the file here? If so, let me know the path to your `.dmp` file.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0cf81bbe-ca55-4a59-9e3a-7adc48d5787d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application and wants to analyze it. Let me think about what tools and approaches are available.\n\nLooking at the available skills, I see there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description says it's for \"Configure and collect crash dumps\" and explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\". So that skill is not appropriate here.\n\nThere are also symbolication skills for Android tombstones and Apple crash logs, but those aren't for .dmp files either.\n\nI should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing a .dmp file. \n\nFor analyzing .NET crash dumps, the main tools available are `dotnet-dump analyze` which works cross-platform, WinDbg with the SOS extension on Windows, or lldb with SOS on Linux and macOS. Since I don't have the dump file yet, I'll need to ask the user where it's located and provide guidance on which tool would be most appropriate for their environment.","outputTokens":692,"requestId":"7647:277795:1A23CC5:1DC0D72:69FE93ED"},"id":"50660117-444c-495e-9ca9-221d44967513","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:55:11.286Z","parentId":"6d5f1378-829d-4914-9e81-f8624464a2b4"}
